<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="260" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/5–2446</note>
                                <head>No. 260<lb/><hi rend="italic">Briefing Book Paper</hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]<note n="1" xml:id="d260fn1">For the full text of this paper, see <ref target="#d525">document No. 525</ref>. The
                                            recommendation here printed also appears in
                                            substantially the same language in <ref target="#d524">document No. 524</ref>.</note></seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Russian Participation in European Economic
                                        Organizations</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">recommendation</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p>It is recommended that we endeavor to obtain agreement from the
                                    Soviet Government to participate fully in … the European Central
                                    Inland Transport Organization (<gloss target="#t_ECITO1">ECITO</gloss>), … including designation of representatives
                                    to cooperate in the day-to-day activities of these
                                    organizations.</p>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">discussion</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                                <p>… Principally due to disagreement on the issue of Polish
                                    representation, the Soviets have not participated in recent
                                    discussions concerning the <gloss target="#t_ECITO1">ECITO</gloss>. Their delegation in London, however, has
                                    informally indicated that the present agreement<note n="2" xml:id="d260fn2">For the text of the agreement as signed on
                                        September 27, 1945, see Executive Agreement Series No. 494;
                                        59 <gloss target="#t_Stat1">Stat</gloss>. (2) 1740.</note>
                                    has substantially met the objections which they had to earlier
                                    drafts. …</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-03">July 3, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>